Somehow Robb and I got on the topic of two-finger scrolling in Linux, the other day.

Now, being a Mac user, I'm rather used to pixel-precision two-finger scrolling...

Here's what you usually get in Linux:

<a href="http://vimeo.com/2561437">Bad scrolling</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user1052518">Robert Carr</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.

Here's what you get now, with Robb's patch to Gtk and the Synaptics driver:

<a href="http://vimeo.com/2561506">Awesome scrolling</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user1052518">Robert Carr</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.

<a href="http://blogs.gnome.org/racarr/2009/01/22/scrolling/">Read more on Robb's blog.</a>

P.S. The browser he's using there is our currently-under-development 'complete' <a href="http://bazaar.launchpad.net/~orange-owners/orange/seed-browser/files">Seed browser</a>.